  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Despite this shortfall the assessment team declared assurance level Medium, supported by strong performance across the remaining twelve factors and agreement within the 10% QoI acceptance bound for all three quantities of interest. Model risk level 3 with medium model influence and medium decision consequence.",
