      "acceptanceCriteria": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 used under FDA-validated installation qualification. Version-controlled solver settings archived in the study repository. QA documentation reviewed and approved by the modeling team lead.",
      "rationale": "The commercial FEA solver is under formal software quality assurance with documented installation qualification, operational qualification, and performance qualification records. All simulation scripts are version-controlled under Git with tagged releases. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions (Timoshenko beam, Hertzian contact) reproduced within 1% relative error. Patch test passed for all element types employed.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical has been verified against standard benchmark problems documented in the NAFEMS suite. Internal code verification benchmarks for beam bending and contact mechanics confirm correct implementation of the element formulations used in this model. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change < 2% between medium and fine mesh. Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI < 5% for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted (coarse ~85k elements, medium ~210k elements, fine ~540k elements). The Grid Convergence Index for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement were 1.8%, 2.3%, and 2.1% respectively, all below the 5% threshold. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nonlinear solver residuals converge to < 1e-6 for force and moment equilibrium at each load step. No spurious energy generation detected.",
      "rationale": "Implicit nonlinear solution with Newton-Raphson iteration converged to force residual norm < 1e-7 for all 200 load steps. Energy balance check confirms no artificial energy dissipation. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments completed by a second modeler not involved in model construction. Discrepancies resolved prior to result extraction.",
      "rationale": "A documented independent review of the model setup was performed by a senior biomechanics engineer. Boundary condition application, contact pair definitions, and material property assignments were verified against the modeling protocol. Two minor discrepancies in contact stiffness settings were identified and corrected. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics assumptions (linear elasticity for UHMWPE blocks, elastic-plastic for titanium alloy) justified by literature and material coupon data. Frictional contact at screw-rod interface validated against published tribological data.",
      "rationale": "The model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model for the Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw based on published tensile coupon data. UHMWPE vertebral body simulant blocks are modeled as linear elastic, consistent with the small-strain regime observed experimentally. Frictional contact coefficient of 0.25 is consistent with published metal-on-metal interface data for titanium alloys. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile testing of the same material batch used in physical constructs. Geometric dimensions measured from CMM inspection of three representative screws.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and ultimate tensile strength (950 MPa) for Ti-6Al-4V were obtained from lot-specific tensile testing performed by the device manufacturer. Rod diameter and screw geometry were measured using coordinate measuring machine inspection, with deviations from nominal < 0.02 mm. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs drawn from a single production lot. Dimensional inspection confirms all constructs within manufacturing tolerances. Coefficient of variation for experimental stiffness < 8%.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from a single production lot and inspected prior to testing. Dimensional measurements confirm all key features within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Experimental stiffness coefficient of variation was 5.3%, indicating acceptable inter-specimen variability. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading rates and environmental conditions, or sensitivity analysis demonstrates insensitivity of QoIs to these variables.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single displacement rate (25 mm/min) under ambient conditions, consistent with ASTM F1717 requirements. However, no variation in loading rate or environmental condition (e.g., simulated body fluid, temperature) was explored, and no sensitivity analysis was performed to bound the effect of these variables on the three QoIs. This factor falls one gradation below the required level 3. The assessment team acknowledged this shortfall but judged that the ASTM F1717 standardized protocol inherently controls test conditions and that rate sensitivity is negligible for quasi-static metallic constructs. Required level 3; achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably correspond to the physical test configuration. Traceability matrix linking model inputs to test measurements provided.",
      "rationale": "A traceability matrix was prepared mapping each model input parameter to its experimental source. Geometric inputs derive from CMM inspection of test constructs; material inputs derive from lot-specific coupon tests; boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as measured. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for all three QoIs using experimental mean and combined experimental-model uncertainty. E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "The validation metric E/uval was computed for stiffness (0.41), yield force (0.52), and force at 40 mm displacement (0.63), all substantially below the 1.96 threshold. Relative differences between FEA predictions and experimental means were 2.0%, 1.9%, and 2.4% respectively, all within the 10% acceptance bound. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are directly relevant to the COU decision on mechanical performance adequacy of the non-cannulated design.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — are the primary mechanical performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly used in the regulatory submission to characterize the structural performance of the pedicle screw construct. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities replicate the COU geometry, loading mode, and boundary conditions. The validated model is used without extrapolation beyond the validated parameter space.",
      "rationale": "The validation activities directly replicate the COU: same screw design (non-cannulated 7.5 mm), same loading mode (ASTM F1717 compression-bending), same construct configuration. The FEA model is applied within the validated parameter space without geometric or loading extrapolation. Required level 2 achieved."
    }
