    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 credibility factors. Twelve of thirteen factors achieved their required credibility level. The single shortfall — Test conditions (achieved level 2 versus required level 3) — was judged acceptable given the ASTM F1717 standardized protocol and the negligible rate sensitivity expected for quasi-static metallic constructs. All three QoIs satisfied the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria (relative difference < 10%; E/uval < 1.96). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU at assurance level Medium.",
